The paper discusses representation sharing in Prolog, which is a programming language falling under the category of logic programming. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses techniques for memory optimization, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the WAM (Warren Abstract Machine), which is a virtual machine used for executing Prolog programs, and therefore, the paper may also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
